<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<ModMetaData>
  <name>Pawn Diary: Rimpsyche</name>
  <author>aimmlegate</author>
  <packageId>aimmlegate.pawndiary.adapter.rimpsyche</packageId>
  <modVersion IgnoreIfNoMatchingField="True">0.1.0</modVersion>
  <supportedVersions>
    <li>1.6</li>
  </supportedVersions>
  <!-- Both are true assembly/load-order dependencies:
       - Pawn Diary owns the public integration API and DiaryInteractionGroupDef XML type.
       - Rimpsyche owns RimPsyche.dll, whose documented personality tracker this adapter reads.
       Harmony is supplied transitively by Rimpsyche's own hard dependency and is never bundled. -->
  <modDependencies>
    <li>
      <packageId>aimmlegate.pawndiary</packageId>
      <displayName>Pawn Diary</displayName>
      <steamWorkshopUrl>steam://url/CommunityFilePage/3752041535</steamWorkshopUrl>
    </li>
    <li>
      <packageId>Maux36.Rimpsyche</packageId>
      <displayName>Rimpsyche - Personality Core</displayName>
      <steamWorkshopUrl>steam://url/CommunityFilePage/3535112473</steamWorkshopUrl>
    </li>
  </modDependencies>
  <loadAfter>
    <li>brrainz.harmony</li>
    <li>aimmlegate.pawndiary</li>
    <li>Maux36.Rimpsyche</li>
  </loadAfter>
  <description>Your colonists already have personalities in Rimpsyche. This lets those personalities reach the page.

Everyday talk can fold into daily social notes, stronger exchanges can become their own memories, and a pawn's strongest traits and interests can color their diary outlook without exposing raw stats. Nothing is written back to Rimpsyche.

Requires Pawn Diary and Rimpsyche - Personality Core.</description>
</ModMetaData>
